article.headline: Idaho 59, Montana 58
article.story:
MOSCOW, Idaho (AP) -- Heather Thoelke converted a four-point play
with 2.1 seconds remaining Wednesday to lift Idaho to a 59-58
victory over Montana.

Montana forward Katie Edwards had given the Lady Griz a 58-55
lead on a jumper in the lane with 17 seconds remaining.

Thoelke was fouled on a made 3-pointer and hit the free throw to
seal the win.

Leilani Mitchell led Idaho (4-3) with 26 points, six rebounds
and six assists.

Montana (4-2) led 30-21 at halftime.

The Vandals cut into the lead through the second half, tying the
score at 46 with 7:28 remaining.

Hollie Tyler, who had 15 points and nine rebounds for the Lady
Griz, gave Montana a 54-50 lead with 2:50 remaining.

Mitchell scored the next five points to give Idaho a 55-54 lead
with 1:21 remaining.

Tyler put Montana back up 56-55 with two free throws with 1:05
remaining.

Thoelke finished with 13 points for Idaho, followed by Emily
Faurholt with 11 points and 10 rebounds.

Edwards finished with 10 points for Montana.
